    "For each water molecule in this layer, we calculated the azimuthal angle 𝜃, defined as the angle between the substrate-normal 𝑧-axis and the water molecule's dipole vector.",
    "Using these angles, we constructed a histogram of the orientation distribution with a bin width of 𝛥𝜃 = 1°, spanning from 0° to 180°.",
    "However, in three-dimensional space, the volume of each angular bin depends on 𝜃 due to the spherical coordinate system.",
    "Specifically, the volume element is given by:",
    "For a fixed radial distance and azimuthal symmetry, the probability density 𝑃(𝜃) must account for the geometric factor sin 𝜃."
